						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 894, Āṅgirasa, Bhādrapada</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 972 August.</hi> It refers itself to the reign of the Rāshṭrakūṭa king <hi rend="bold">[Kho]ṭṭigadēva</hi> and mentions his feudatory <hi rend="bold">Permānaḍi</hi> of the <hi rend="bold">Gaṅga</hi> dynasty. It records the gift of some land to a <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> and mentions the Jaina teacher <hi rend="bold">[Ma]hēndradēva-Paṇḍita.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
